<TEXT>&#2;<DATELINE>1985-11-30</DATELINE><TITLE>Revelation through exploitation: the viral model for intracellular traffic</TITLE><BODY>Abstract Enveloped viruses exploit the existing routes of membrane traffic to enter and leave the host cell. The similarity between viral envelopes and cellular membranes has allowed the use of animal viruses as probes to examine aspects of intracellular traffic.&#3;</BODY></TEXT>